entry.title: Russia's Assault on Ukraine Uproots 10 Million People
entry.content: Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin said Russia is deliberately targeting population centers because its military campaign had stalled in the face of an effective Ukrainian defense and counterattack.

entry.title: War in Ukraine Is Already Taking Its Toll on Global Food Supplies
entry.content: Shortages of fuel, fertilizer and workers caused by the Russian invasion will shrink an annual bounty that countries rely on around the world. “We want to plant, but the situation is totally unpredictable.”

entry.title: Elon Musk's Business Ties to China Create Unease in Washington
entry.content: Tesla and SpaceX are at the center of discussions, with some lawmakers fearing Beijing could access secrets.

entry.title: China Says Housing Prices Are Stable, but Developers See Significant Declines
entry.content: One main reason for the diverging picture is the composition of the country’s official data, economists and property analysts say.
